The paper discusses the repetitiveness of natural code and how it is written in certain preferred ways that would be familiar to code readers. This suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as the primary sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the expressive nature of programming languages (cs.PL) and uses language models to analyze code (cs.LG). Finally, the paper includes a human subject study (cs.HC) to support their findings.
